history.content: If you've previously taken two project-heavy and/or four technical classes, I'd say go ahead with your class schedule. Otherwise, since you're finishing up your lower division CS requirements anyway, I would recommend taking 168 after CS 61C.

Is it ok to take these two courses concurrently, or would you recommend taking 168 next semester after I take 61C?

I'm currently enrolled in 61C, 168, 194-26 (Image Manipulation & Computational Photography), and Music 158A (tech elective). Do you think this is doable, considering 168 and 194 are both project heavy?
